pathParameters.name: messageId
pathParameters.description: when not set, returns the next unhandled message

object.name: Any
object.description:
Any is wire-compatible with google.protobuf.Any, but without the parsing and
encoding methods, i.e. it leaves proto messages proto bytes

properties.name: replyTo
properties.description:
In the reply to a request/reply message, Identifies the service or instance
which first sent the request to which the reply should be routed.

enum.name: WireEncoding
enum.description: WireEncoding specifies the encoding of the value field in the Any message

options.name: RAW
options.description: Raw message of any format. Maps to /o5.messaging.v1.topic.RawMessageTopic/Raw

object.name: Message
object.description:
Message wraps messaging content for the underlying platform routing and
delivery.

properties.name: grpcMethod
properties.description: The short name of the method in the gRPC service

properties.name: sourceApp
properties.description: Then o5.application.name which sent the message

properties.name: sourceEnv
properties.description: The o5.environment.full_name which sent the message

properties.name: destinationTopic
properties.description: compatibility with named topic messaging, specifies the destination name

properties.name: timestamp
properties.description: Timestamp when producing or replaying the message.

properties.name: headers
properties.description:
Message wraps messaging content for the underlying platform routing and
delivery.

properties.name: replyTo
properties.description: Copied from the Request's reply_to field when replying.

properties.name: deathId
properties.description:
Generated by the handler on failure, so that multiple failures of the same
message (either through replay or multiple services working on the same
cause) are not de-duplicated. This is used as the message_id on the wire
message when sent, the original message_id is in the message field.

properties.name: handlerApp
properties.description: The o5.application.name which attepmted to handle the message

properties.name: handlerEnv
properties.description: The o5.environment.full_name which attepmted to handle the message

properties.name: message
properties.description: The message which was not able to be handled

properties.name: problem
properties.description: The problem which caused the message to die
